<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1503] Solr throws 500 instead of 400 on some malformed requests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1503</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you submit a malformed xml document to update, Solr returns a 500 error.  Clients often treat this as a failure in the server, but it&apos;s really a 400 invalid request.  Trivial patch is attached, although there may be similar cases (i.e. malformed json) that are also worth investigating.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
